Program: Omnibus
Title: Fall of a Fortress - Part One
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mcv
Last Broadcast Date: 25 February 2002
In 1942, the Japanese army entered and occupied Singapore, "the impregnable fortress". It was a military disaster for Britain. Survivors give their testimony, including a rare interview with the creator of post-war Singapore, Lee Kuan Yew. Presented by Piers Plowright